# 🧭 Community Resource Directory: Free & Low-Cost Help Services

A curated list of websites that help individuals and families across the United States find free or low-cost services such as food assistance, housing, healthcare, mental health support, and more. These platforms are ideal for anyone in need of support or helping others connect to vital resources.

---

## 🌟 Featured: [Findhelp.org](https://www.findhelp.org)
**Description:**  
Findhelp.org (formerly Aunt Bertha) is one of the largest search platforms for finding social care services in the U.S. By entering your ZIP code, you can browse thousands of programs offering food assistance, housing, medical care, job training, legal aid, and more—all free or reduced cost.

---

## 🌐 General Support Services

### [211.org](https://www.211.org)
**Description:**  
A nationwide directory that connects individuals to essential services such as housing, food, healthcare, mental health support, and disaster assistance. Operated by United Way.

---

### [Benefits.gov](https://www.benefits.gov)
**Description:**  
The U.S. government’s official benefits website. Provides a guided questionnaire to help users identify eligible federal and state benefit programs.

---

### [NeedHelpPayingBills.com](https://www.needhelppayingbills.com)
**Description:**  
Offers comprehensive information about local programs to help with rent, utilities, groceries, medical bills, and more. Resources are organized by city and state.

---

## 🏠 Housing & Homeless Assistance

### [Homeless Shelter Directory](https://www.homelessshelterdirectory.org)
**Description:**  
A database of homeless shelters, transitional housing, and food banks across the United States. Searchable by city and state.

---

## 💬 Mental Health & Recovery

### [GetHelp.com](https://www.gethelp.com)
**Description:**  
Connects users to local mental health professionals, therapy services, crisis lines, and recovery resources.

---

## 👩‍👧 Support for Mothers and Families

### [Single Mother Guide](https://singlemotherguide.com)
**Description:**  
Dedicated to helping single mothers access financial assistance, housing support, scholarships, childcare, and more.

---

## 👵 Senior Support

### [SHARE (Self-Help for the Elderly)](https://www.share.org)
**Description:**  
Provides resources and services for seniors, including nutrition programs, housing referrals, and in-home support.

---
